==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[éolipyle]], from Latin ''Aeoli pylae'' ‘doorway of [[Aeolus]]’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'i:əʊlɪpʌɪl/

===Noun===
'''aeolipile'''
# an instrument used to demonstrate the force at which heated vapour escapes from a vessel through a narow aperture

